  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">• Optical analogy of electrons' behavior has been used for generating giant persistent currents. • We change optical waveguide networks into symmetric defect mesoscopic-ring networks (SDMRNs). • We give out the sufficient condition for generating maximum persistent current <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mo stretchy="false">|</mo><msub><mrow><mi>J</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mo stretchy="false">|</mo></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">max</mi></mrow></msub></math> in SDMRNs. • We find the relationship between <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mo stretchy="false">|</mo><msub><mrow><mi>J</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mo stretchy="false">|</mo></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">max</mi></mrow></msub></math> and electronic localizations and obtain the formula of <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mo stretchy="false">|</mo><msub><mrow><mi>J</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mo stretchy="false">|</mo></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">max</mi></mrow></msub></math> . • <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mo stretchy="false">|</mo><msub><mrow><mi>J</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mo stretchy="false">|</mo></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">max</mi></mrow></msub></math> can be enhanced by changing structural parameters of SDMRNs.</subfield>
